The paper deals with the design of auctions, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT) and falls under the broader area of algorithmic mechanism design. The use of competitive analysis framework suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the optimization of worst-case performance, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with revenue generation, which is a key aspect of economic theory and mechanism design (cs.EC).
